  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Regular financial audits\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulated Sectors:\n- Banking\n- Financial services\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate\n- Casino and gambling industries\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing strict regulatory standards and reporting requirements.",
